'use strict';

const parsers = {
    argsListPart: require('./argsListPart'),
    betweenPart: require('./betweenPart'),
    escapePart: require('./escapePart'),
    ilriPart: require('./ilriPart'),
    inArgsListPart: require('./inArgsListPart'),
    inExprPart: require('./inExprPart'),
    isPart: require('./isPart'),
    likePart: require('./likePart'),
    overlapsPart: require('./overlapsPart'),
    regexpPart: require('./regexpPart')
};

const partials = options => Object.keys(parsers).reduce((result, current) => {
    return Object.assign({}, result, { [current]: parsers[current].parser(options) });
}, {});

partials.Type = Object.keys(parsers).reduce((result, current) => {
    return Object.assign({}, result, { [parsers[current].name]: current });
}, {});

module.exports = partials;
